## Appending Elements

```js 
const newElement = document.createElement("h1");
//  Add Text Content
newElement.innerText = "Text Inside H1";
//  Add Text This way too
newElement.textContent = "This text also works";
//  Add ClassName
newElement.className = "header";
//  Select Parent
const parentElement = document.getElementById("root");
//  Add New Element to Parent
parentElement.appendChild(newElement);
//  This also works
parentElement.append(newElement);
```


## Text Styling

:::tip
- inner text and InnerHTML are the best choices
- innerText returns the string context already arranged
- innerHTML returns the a string with HTML tags and indents
- textContent Returns innerHTML without the tags and indents, very shitty
:::



